  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Targeted Assistance to the Community of Tchirozerine/Projet d&#x2019;Assistance Cibl&#xE9;e aux Communaut&#xE9;s de Tchirozerine (PACT)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal: Enhanced food security and economic recovery for disaster-affected communities in Tchirozerine Department.

Objectives:
1.	Increase vulnerable households&#x2019; access to food during the lean season
2.	Restore market gardening production in target areas
3.	Better prepare communities for future flood or drought-related disasters</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project responds to the emergency situation in the Tchirozerine Department of Niger (Agadez region), which has been significantly affected by multi-year food crises, devastating floods, a recent influx of repatriated Nigeriens from Libya, drought-related price inflation, and potential destabilization from Touareg communities in Mali. With its five years of experience in Agadez, Mercy Corps will build upon the foundation of activities carried out under the OFDA-funded RESTOR  project, as well as expertise gained through the implementation of local and regional food procurement and distribution in the target area. The goal of the proposed intervention is to increase the resiliency of 1000 households (6,650 individuals) who require immediate assistance to meet their basic needs and restore their livelihoods. 
This project will complement Mercy Corps&#x2019; intervention proposed to the World Food Program (WFP), consisting of cash distributions to 6,279 households in urban Agadez.</narrative>
  </description>
